OL,10,Fcare system cope during the pandemic",
OL,11,Fthe speed and volume of applications
OL,12,F"came at a painfully high cost ` to
OL,13,Fthe safety of workers from the
OL,14,Fdepredations of labour market abuses,
OL,15,Fand the integrity of the system from
OL,16,Fpeople not following the rules".
OL,18,FHe added: "There has long been
OL,19,Fmounting evidence of serious issues
OL,20,Fwith the system, laid bare once again
